Minister of Health Zweli Mkhize briefs media following meeting with private health sector. JOHANNESBURG – Health Minister Zweli Mkhize is briefing the media on the latest COVID-19 related issues. Mkhize will be joined by KwaZulu Natal Health MEC Nomagugu Simelane-Zulu. The minister and the MEC have met with CEOs of private hospital groups. Government is trying to establish better working relations during the COVID-19 pandemic. READ: COVID-19: African countries heading for peak in cases There are currently 18 fatalities in South Africa. Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.